Package: CurVol
Type: Package
Title: Curve Data Volatility Analysis
Version: 2.0.0
Author: Kelly Ramsay, Gregory Rice, Tony Wirjanto, Yuqian Zhao
Maintainer: Yuqian Zhao <y.zhao@essex.ac.uk>
Description: Functional time series data derived from financial markets exhibit conditional heteroscedasticity. Tests and models have been developed to depicit this property in a series of papers by 
             Hormann et al., (2013) <doi:10.1017/S0266466612000345>, 
             Aue et al., (2017) <doi:10.1111/jtsa.12192>, 
             Cerovecki et al., (2019) <doi:10.1016/j.jeconom.2019.01.006>, 
             Rice et al., (2020) <doi:10.1111/jtsa.12532>, 
             Rice et al., (2020) <doi:10.1016/j.ijforecast.2019.10.006>. 
             Rice et al., (2021) <https://mpra.ub.uni-muenchen.de/109231>. MPRA Paper No. 109231.
             These procedures enable data generating processes, functional GARCH-type model estimation, goodness-of-fit tests, and backtesting methods.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
